Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:20,540 --> 00:00:21,090
Hey.

6
00:00:21,130 --> 00:00:22,310
Pick the ball up for me.

7
00:00:23,220 --> 00:00:24,410
Don’t you even want to say sorry?

8
00:00:24,450 --> 00:00:25,180
I won’t.

9
00:00:25,420 --> 00:00:26,050
Fine.

10
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:29,920
Ouch!

11
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:30,880
Where’s your friend?

12
00:00:30,910 --> 00:00:32,680
Take me to meet him now.

13
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:34,910
Damn it.

14
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:36,910
Bear in mind how much you messed with me.

15
00:00:36,950 --> 00:00:37,620
Come.

16
00:00:38,370 --> 00:00:39,040
I’m sorry.

17
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,770
You must compensate for hurting me.

18
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:41,330
[Vat 7%]
[Total cost]

19
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:42,290
200K?

20
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:43,280
I can’t afford to pay.

21
00:00:43,330 --> 00:00:46,730
You must compensate with something else, then.

22
00:02:04,730 --> 00:02:08,389
DIRECTED BY SIWAJ SAWATMANEEKUL

23
00:02:14,390 --> 00:02:18,770
(Huuhh. I never expected my peaceful life to be disrupted like this.)

24
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,650
(It’s all because of this guy.)

25
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:27,110
[Vat 7%]
[Total cost]

26
00:02:27,370 --> 00:02:28,740
200K?

27
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,390
I can’t afford to pay 200K.

28
00:02:35,620 --> 00:02:39,570
You must compensate with something else, then.

29
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:41,500
Like what?

30
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,600
Be my slave.

31
00:02:58,710 --> 00:02:59,900
Are you kidding me?

32
00:03:01,830 --> 00:03:02,870
I’m serious.

33
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,980
Serve me for two months,

34
00:03:06,340 --> 00:03:07,600
and we’re good.

35
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:09,200
Why must I do it?

36
00:03:09,590 --> 00:03:11,200
Pay me, then.

37
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:13,330
The choice is yours.

38
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:15,140
Choose whether you want to do it or not.

39
00:03:15,190 --> 00:03:16,430
Whatever pleases you.

40
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:17,900
Thanks a lot.

41
00:03:17,940 --> 00:03:20,380
I never felt this pleased before in my life.

42
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:23,840
I can take payment in four installments if you want.

43
00:03:23,890 --> 00:03:26,170
See how kind I am to you?

44
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:29,329
You wrecked my drawing,

45
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,460
but you didn’t own up to it.

46
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:32,220
You didn’t even simply say sorry to me.

47
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,100
How much is it?

48
00:03:36,370 --> 00:03:37,750
How much is your drawing?

49
00:03:37,780 --> 00:03:38,829
I’ll pay you now.

50
00:03:40,730 --> 00:03:41,680
You’re just…

51
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:43,970
a rich brat.

52
00:03:44,890 --> 00:03:46,750
Don’t talk too much.

53
00:03:46,790 --> 00:03:48,090
It’s your call.

54
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:50,340
Pay up

55
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:51,690
or agree to do as I say.

56
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,320
Two months is too long.

57
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,160
I’ll do that until

58
00:03:59,690 --> 00:04:02,260
I’ve finished repainting the work you ruined.

59
00:04:04,090 --> 00:04:05,280
What if you just cut corners

60
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:06,580
and finish it in a couple of days?

61
00:04:06,630 --> 00:04:07,000
Hey.

62
00:04:07,030 --> 00:04:08,450
What kind of person do you think I am, huh?

63
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,620
It took me several weeks to finish the painting

64
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:12,250
that a random dog just ruined.

65
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,160
I won’t cut corners.

66
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:15,730
Fine.

67
00:04:18,339 --> 00:04:19,740
But we’ll be doing this under one condition.

68
00:04:19,940 --> 00:04:20,589
What is it?

69
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:24,430
Don’t tell anyone I’m your slave.

70
00:04:24,460 --> 00:04:26,010
Don’t even let Tan find out.

71
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:31,470
Deal.

72
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:36,790
Deal.

73
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:44,400
Let go already.

74
00:04:45,580 --> 00:04:46,400
Follow me.

75
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:47,810
Where to?

76
00:04:48,370 --> 00:04:49,900
To do your job.

77
00:04:50,330 --> 00:04:50,909
Huh?

78
00:04:51,250 --> 00:04:52,000
Don’t talk too much.

79
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:52,880
Just follow me.

80
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:53,600
Hurry up.

81
00:05:00,330 --> 00:05:01,900
Where are you taking me?

82
00:05:03,620 --> 00:05:05,160
Hey, talk to me.

83
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:06,410
Where are you taking me?

84
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,370
Fine.

85
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,870
You’re being like this, huh?

86
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:13,700
But bear this in mind.

87
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,770
If something happens to me,

88
00:05:15,830 --> 00:05:17,090
you’re toast

89
00:05:17,110 --> 00:05:19,390
because those three are witnesses.

90
00:05:19,430 --> 00:05:20,840
They saw me come with you.

91
00:05:21,170 --> 00:05:22,390
I’m not threatening you

92
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:23,520
but just want to let you know

93
00:05:23,550 --> 00:05:24,510
I’m not a puppet on a string

94
00:05:24,540 --> 00:05:25,810
that you can do away with easily.

95
00:05:26,210 --> 00:05:27,460
What are you talking about?

96
00:05:27,930 --> 00:05:30,240
Also, why would a puppet be on a string?

97
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,159
Alright then.

98
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:38,820
Just talk to me reasonably

99
00:05:38,870 --> 00:05:39,850
like how a civilized person does.

100
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:40,730
Got it?

101
00:05:47,340 --> 00:05:48,100
Please.

102
00:05:48,130 --> 00:05:48,810
Okay?

103
00:05:50,409 --> 00:05:55,480
I admit we both screwed up that day.

104
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,840
You couldn’t control yourself,

105
00:05:57,870 --> 00:06:00,450
while I let my emotions take over too much.

106
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,950
So, since we already screwed up,

107
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:04,720
we couldn’t turn back time to fix it.

108
00:06:04,740 --> 00:06:08,040
But what we can do is keep moving forward

109
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:10,040
because such a thing won’t happen again.

110
00:06:10,260 --> 00:06:11,090
Starting today, I promise

111
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:13,340
we’ll turn into strangers

112
00:06:13,370 --> 00:06:16,770
and pretend this whole thing never happened.

113
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:19,920
The story about us will just remain a memory.

114
00:06:19,970 --> 00:06:20,790
Okay?

115
00:06:22,110 --> 00:06:22,750
What story?

116
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:27,000
The story between us.

117
00:06:33,690 --> 00:06:34,670
Drop it.

118
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:36,270
You’re annoying me.

119
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,870
Can we head back already?

120
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:51,700
I’ll just swing by a few more shops.

121
00:06:53,190 --> 00:06:54,780
A few more?

122
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:55,800
Hey.

123
00:06:55,830 --> 00:06:57,520
Why did you buy so much stuff?

124
00:06:57,570 --> 00:06:58,440
Look.

125
00:06:58,470 --> 00:06:59,600
It’s freaking a lot.

126
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:00,280
Just carry them.

127
00:07:00,310 --> 00:07:01,390
Stop complaining.

128
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:04,350
Why?

129
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:05,810
It’s just carrying stuff, but you’re tired already?

130
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:06,620
Whoa.

131
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,760
I’m just carrying stuff but already tired?

132
00:07:07,790 --> 00:07:09,560
You’re shopping as if you’re trying to empty out the entire mall.

133
00:07:19,410 --> 00:07:21,880
Peem, you’re back?

134
00:07:22,230 --> 00:07:22,870
Yeah.

135
00:07:23,470 --> 00:07:25,930
Oh, look at you.

136
00:07:25,970 --> 00:07:27,320
You look exhausted.

137
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,770
Have you been hitting the books hard?

138
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,180
No, Auntie.

139
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:33,430
My university buddy made me haul his stuff around all day today.

140
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:35,280
Who?

141
00:07:35,490 --> 00:07:36,600
Who dared to do that to my nephew?

142
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:37,030
Tell me.

143
00:07:37,050 --> 00:07:38,060
I’ll handle him.

144
00:07:38,090 --> 00:07:39,180
Just forget about it.

145
00:07:40,909 --> 00:07:41,700
Where are you off to?

146
00:07:41,730 --> 00:07:42,560
Grandma’s place?

147
00:07:42,570 --> 00:07:43,730
Yes.

148
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:44,880
I’ll be right back.

149
00:07:44,890 --> 00:07:46,340
Sure.

150
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:50,720
Don’t just drink with your friends on the weekend.

151
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:52,430
Yes, sir.

152
00:07:56,210 --> 00:07:57,040
That’s obvious.

153
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:58,409
That’s obvious.

154
00:08:02,710 --> 00:08:04,770
I’ll come home no later than 6 AM.

155
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,760
Look after the shop for me.

156
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:08,960
Lock the door.

157
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:09,820
Look after my shop

158
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,370
and my house, Peem.

159
00:08:11,410 --> 00:08:12,470
Help me, okay?

160
00:08:27,250 --> 00:08:28,750
Peem, wake up already.

161
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:29,630
Peem!

162
00:08:30,050 --> 00:08:30,630
Hey!

163
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,240
Peem!

164
00:08:32,909 --> 00:08:33,659
Peem.

165
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:35,840
Wake up.

166
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:38,360
I think we must do something.

167
00:08:39,429 --> 00:08:41,429
One, two, three.

168
00:08:41,460 --> 00:08:42,799
Peem!

169
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,240
Gosh.

170
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:46,360
What do you want from me, huh?

171
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,170
What’s up?

172
00:08:48,210 --> 00:08:49,630
Come on.

173
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:51,660
I’m worried about you.

174
00:08:51,690 --> 00:08:53,290
You didn’t pick up my calls.

175
00:08:53,330 --> 00:08:55,990
I thought Phum randomly ditched you somewhere.

176
00:08:56,020 --> 00:08:57,020
Don’t even say a single word.

177
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,290
You got me into a real mess, Tan.

178
00:08:58,330 --> 00:08:59,500
Don’t mention his name.

179
00:08:59,530 --> 00:09:00,530
I’m up in arms.

180
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:02,310
I didn’t do anything, buddy.

181
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,750
So, what did Phum talk to you about?

182
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:09,210
Nothing.

183
00:09:09,220 --> 00:09:10,100
He didn’t do anything.

184
00:09:10,110 --> 00:09:10,900
Nothing much.

185
00:09:10,940 --> 00:09:11,380
We just hashed things out.

186
00:09:11,420 --> 00:09:12,080
That’s it.

187
00:09:13,490 --> 00:09:14,640
Are you sure?

188
00:09:14,690 --> 00:09:16,240
He dragged you that hard.

189
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:17,570
He didn’t do anything to you?

190
00:09:19,570 --> 00:09:21,000
Why is nobody believing me?

191
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:22,320
There’s really nothing to worry about.

192
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,400
We already cleared things up.

193
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,570
What are you guys talking about?

194
00:09:26,620 --> 00:09:27,020
Eh?

195
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,760
You tagged along

196
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:30,920
but you had no clue what happened?

197
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:31,980
Uh-huh.

198
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,370
But I think it’s fun,

199
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,070
so I came along.

200
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,660
Tell me about it.

201
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:37,610
Please.

202
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:38,180
Please.

203
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:38,880
Long story short.

204
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:40,070
Nothing much, everyone.

205
00:09:40,090 --> 00:09:41,330
He dragged me there,

206
00:09:41,350 --> 00:09:42,470
and we talked it out.

207
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:43,490
We cleared things up.

208
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:43,920
It’s all water under the bridge now.

209
00:09:43,970 --> 00:09:45,040
Really?

210
00:09:45,490 --> 00:09:47,850
Could someone like Phum let it slide this easily?

211
00:09:54,430 --> 00:09:56,430
What are you implying?

212
00:09:56,930 --> 00:09:58,120
Tan!

213
00:09:58,780 --> 00:10:01,280
You knew from the start he would do something to me, didn’t you?!

214
00:10:01,330 --> 00:10:03,280
But you still brought him over?

215
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:07,170
My bad. I’m sorry.

216
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,370
You’re done for.

217
00:10:09,670 --> 00:10:10,740
Nothing happened, seriously?

218
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:11,950
Nothing at all.

219
00:10:11,990 --> 00:10:12,880
I said that already.

220
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,350
Don’t you understand what I said?

221
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:16,400
Just forget about it.

222
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,530
Let’s cook, shall we?

223
00:10:17,580 --> 00:10:18,540
Auntie is not home.

224
00:10:20,180 --> 00:10:21,180
Good idea.

225
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:24,120
Today, Tan’s on a mission to show off his cooking prowess.

226
00:10:26,710 --> 00:10:27,530
Eh?

227
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:28,680
With his bare hands, you know.

228
00:10:29,610 --> 00:10:30,990
Make sure it’s delicious.

229
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:31,940
Sure thing.

230
00:10:31,980 --> 00:10:33,270
I guarantee you will enjoy how delicious it is

231
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:34,310
though it doesn’t meet food hygiene standards.

232
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,080
If you mess it up,

233
00:10:36,130 --> 00:10:37,040
I’ll give you a double serving of trouble.

234
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,150
Give me three.

235
00:10:38,180 --> 00:10:39,960
Right here.

236
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,610
I’m kidding.

237
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:43,170
Do you remember this friend of yours?

238
00:10:49,110 --> 00:10:51,110
Phum really didn’t do anything to you?

239
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,950
You’re still curious?

240
00:10:55,170 --> 00:10:56,880
From what I know of him,

241
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:59,520
Phum is not one to let things slide easily.

242
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:01,190
Why?

243
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:03,190
What did you expect him to do to me?

244
00:11:04,350 --> 00:11:05,090
I don’t know.

245
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,080
Well,

246
00:11:08,140 --> 00:11:10,440
we buried the hatchet.

247
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,100
That’s it.

248
00:11:11,110 --> 00:11:11,920
Got it?

249
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:15,520
But Tan told me

250
00:11:15,580 --> 00:11:17,650
Phum kicked the ball right into your painting.

251
00:11:17,690 --> 00:11:18,700
He did.

252
00:11:18,730 --> 00:11:19,790
It got stained all over.

253
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:22,890
The deadline is approaching.

254
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:24,650
How will he make it right?

255
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,300
Be my slave.

256
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:34,150
Well, he just paid me.

257
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:35,170
That’s it.

258
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,280
End of story.

259
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:41,520
Hey, Pun!

260
00:11:41,990 --> 00:11:42,960
What are you doing?

261
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,690
You just splashed oil all over me.

262
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,480
Eh? We’re cooking Water Spinach Stir-Fry,

263
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,390
so, we must flip it in the air, mustn’t we?

264
00:11:47,420 --> 00:11:49,280
Come on, Pun.

265
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,990
We’ll just flip it at the end.

266
00:11:52,020 --> 00:11:54,080
Did you really think having Pun help you was a good idea?

267
00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:57,110
Dude, I didn’t ask for his help.

268
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:58,260
He just barged in.

269
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,270
You aren’t going to set my house on fire, are you?

270
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:01,920
Come on, dude.

271
00:12:01,970 --> 00:12:03,090
If that happens,

272
00:12:03,130 --> 00:12:07,100
I’ll call the fire department to put the fire out.

273
00:12:07,340 --> 00:12:08,080
Here we go.

274
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:12,650
Hey!

275
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:13,790
See?

276
00:12:13,890 --> 00:12:15,340
The pan is on fire!

277
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:17,340
I’m the master.

278
00:12:17,950 --> 00:12:19,970
Customers, please wait for it.

279
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:21,140
This chef will serve you this dish shortly.

280
00:12:21,170 --> 00:12:21,710
Should we add some more?

281
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:22,490
No, we won’t.

282
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:22,960
You silly.

283
00:12:22,980 --> 00:12:23,650
We’re good.

284
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:24,490
Hey.

285
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:26,260
Pun, just sit down and wait for it.

286
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:26,970
What are you standing here for?

287
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:27,650
In case you need more water spinach.

288
