308
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:13,560
The crispy pork is superb.

309
00:13:13,590 --> 00:13:13,850
How is it?

310
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:14,820
Super tasty, huh?

311
00:13:15,170 --> 00:13:16,070
I bought it down the alley.

312
00:13:16,090 --> 00:13:16,770
What?

313
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,200
Just enjoy it.

314
00:13:19,230 --> 00:13:19,870
Go ahead.

315
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,100
It’s delicious.

316
00:13:55,060 --> 00:13:55,870
Gotcha.

317
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,120
Tan!

318
00:13:57,150 --> 00:13:57,980
That’s my crispy pork!

319
00:13:59,980 --> 00:14:00,470
It’s mine.

320
00:14:00,490 --> 00:14:00,950
It’s mine.

321
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:02,160
It’s mine.

322
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:02,680
It’s mine.

323
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:04,730
It’s mine.

324
00:14:05,970 --> 00:14:06,560
Tan!

325
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:10,810
I’m the winner.

326
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,260
Tan!

327
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:17,990
Throw up.

328
00:14:18,010 --> 00:14:18,840
I’ll eat it.

329
00:14:21,230 --> 00:14:23,360
Your food is here.

330
00:14:23,410 --> 00:14:25,360
Your food is here.

331
00:14:25,410 --> 00:14:27,580
Come take what you ordered.

332
00:14:27,590 --> 00:14:28,510
Don’t forget to pay.

333
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:29,360
I’ve got it noted down.

334
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:30,030
I’m broke.

335
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:31,310
I won’t pay.

336
00:14:31,340 --> 00:14:32,620
You’re in for it, dude.

337
00:14:32,650 --> 00:14:33,910
Pay me now.

338
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:35,220
I’m already broke this month.

339
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,000
Come.

340
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:36,930
Grab yours.

341
00:14:39,140 --> 00:14:40,280
Come.

342
00:14:45,540 --> 00:14:46,970
Did you get any sleep?

343
00:14:50,660 --> 00:14:52,240
How amazing you are, buddy.

344
00:15:04,990 --> 00:15:06,990
Professor Po is coming at 9 AM.

345
00:15:07,410 --> 00:15:09,170
Where is Fai?

346
00:15:10,420 --> 00:15:11,940
She had an upset stomach,  so she went home.

347
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:15,550
Poor us.

348
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:21,730
Give me one more.

349
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:24,240
Hey. I’m hungry too.

350
00:15:27,350 --> 00:15:28,510
Show me yours.

351
00:15:30,510 --> 00:15:31,520
What’s this?

352
00:15:37,060 --> 00:15:38,080
What’s wrong?

353
00:15:41,180 --> 00:15:42,300
I don’t know.

354
00:15:43,690 --> 00:15:45,530
I just feel my work is still not good enough.

355
00:15:55,290 --> 00:15:56,850
Professor Po will help you.

356
00:16:02,070 --> 00:16:02,860
I’ll make instant noodles.

357
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:03,140
Need one?

358
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:03,470
Nope.

359
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:04,090
Go ahead.

360
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:09,520
How is it going, Peem?

361
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:20,380
Well, it looks interesting,

362
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:24,500
but I still don’t quite get your concept.

363
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:27,040
But after you finish it,

364
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,800
I think I’ll have a clearer picture.

365
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:30,990
By the way, Peem,

366
00:16:31,530 --> 00:16:33,280
I’ve seen many times

367
00:16:33,870 --> 00:16:36,940
that your work often involves water and canals.

368
00:16:36,970 --> 00:16:38,470
Do you have a specific reason for that?

369
00:16:39,280 --> 00:16:41,160
I personally like rivers.

370
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,160
I enjoy watching the water keep flowing.

371
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,170
When I stare at it for a long time,

372
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,430
I’ll feel at ease.

373
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:49,130
It feels like I’m flowing with it.

374
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:52,050
That’s why I often involve it in my art

375
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,800
to show how it affects my emotions.

376
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:57,730
Ah, I see.

377
00:16:59,990 --> 00:17:04,680
Prof, do you think my work is too simple?

378
00:17:05,569 --> 00:17:06,720
Simple?

379
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:08,930
That’s a tricky question.

380
00:17:09,569 --> 00:17:10,520
Why, Peem?

381
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:11,960
Well,

382
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:20,069
I feel my art delivers messages directly.

383
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:23,000
Like, comparing to other classmates’

384
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:25,150
such as Q’s,

385
00:17:25,339 --> 00:17:29,960
which is complex, deep, and needs interpretation,

386
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:33,570
I think his work looks majestic and valuable.

387
00:17:33,980 --> 00:17:37,500
Peem, are you telling me that,

388
00:17:37,530 --> 00:17:39,040
to label the work as complex,

389
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:42,700
it must be valuable and majestic?

390
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:49,000
Um, maybe?

391
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:51,540
How strange you two are.

392
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,980
I now believe you’re besties.

393
00:17:54,130 --> 00:17:54,750
Eh?

394
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:56,960
Why?

395
00:18:04,190 --> 00:18:05,990
When Q submitted his sketch last time,

396
00:18:06,730 --> 00:18:08,930
he asked a similar question.

397
00:18:09,310 --> 00:18:12,430
He was like, “Prof, is my work too complicated?”

398
00:18:12,470 --> 00:18:14,140
“I’m afraid viewers won’t understand it.”

399
00:18:14,180 --> 00:18:17,150
“I want it more like Peem’s, which conveys a message directly.”

400
00:18:17,180 --> 00:18:18,410
“I want to make it easy to interpret and understand.”

401
00:18:18,460 --> 00:18:19,160
See?

402
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,050
Q said that?

403
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:20,700
He did.

404
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:21,760
Seriously?

405
00:18:21,790 --> 00:18:22,480
Yeah.

406
00:18:22,510 --> 00:18:23,310
You aren’t joking, right?

407
00:18:23,340 --> 00:18:24,310
I’m not joking.

408
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:28,240
I understand that it’s really tough

409
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:30,930
to stop comparing yourself to others.

410
00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:34,780
But I have one question for you, Peem.

411
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:40,720
What’s not good about simplicity?

412
00:18:46,890 --> 00:18:47,920
Think it over.

413
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:51,900
Thank you, Prof.

414
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:53,900
Keep at it.

415
00:18:54,560 --> 00:18:56,100
He’s not sharing it with anyone, huh?

416
00:19:02,230 --> 00:19:03,530
What did he say?

417
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,510
He said it’s okay.

418
00:19:06,590 --> 00:19:08,040
I just have to refine my concept.

419
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,680
Everything else is already on track.

420
00:19:12,290 --> 00:19:13,200
Give me some.

421
00:19:13,340 --> 00:19:14,320
That’s the leftover.

422
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,430
Since the dog didn’t eat it,

423
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:16,360
I will.

424
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:23,190
Peem, hello.

425
00:19:23,220 --> 00:19:24,130
Hey. What brings you here?

426
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:24,780
Q, hello.

427
00:19:24,810 --> 00:19:25,620
Why are you here?

428
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:30,270
Well, we’ve both got a meeting with Professor Po.

429
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:35,280
Peem, that looks so yummy.

430
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:36,240
Let me have a bite.

431
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:36,970
You want some?

432
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:38,800
That’s mine.

433
00:19:40,660 --> 00:19:41,780
I’m not sharing.

434
00:19:41,810 --> 00:19:43,290
Come on, Q.

435
00:19:43,330 --> 00:19:44,440
Let me eat it.

436
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:45,470
Just one bite will do.

437
00:19:45,510 --> 00:19:46,240
No.

438
00:19:49,190 --> 00:19:50,790
Quit teasing him.

439
00:19:50,810 --> 00:19:51,590
Take it, then.

440
00:19:51,610 --> 00:19:52,400
It’s yours, isn’t it?

441
00:19:53,140 --> 00:19:54,180
I’ll make one for you.

442
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:54,830
Don’t worry.

443
00:19:55,130 --> 00:19:55,800
Oho.

444
00:19:56,370 --> 00:19:57,990
Peem is so kind-hearted,

445
00:19:58,270 --> 00:19:59,920
unlike someone here.

446
00:20:04,650 --> 00:20:05,990
Show me your work.

447
00:20:09,220 --> 00:20:09,930
Why?

448
00:20:09,990 --> 00:20:11,440
Why must I do that?

449
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:15,350
Oh, he’s being serious here.

450
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:18,090
Fine.

451
00:20:18,130 --> 00:20:19,200
I’ll show you.

452
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:20,520
Here it is.

453
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:21,210
What do you think?

454
00:20:22,190 --> 00:20:23,130
It’s beautiful, isn’t it?

455
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:28,730
No wonder you’re my mentee.

456
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:29,620
What?

457
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,990
What does that have to do with you?

458
00:20:32,030 --> 00:20:32,810
How could you say it doesn’t?

459
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:34,340
I taught you how to draw like that.

460
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:36,830
I even guided your hand.

461
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,530
How could you say it’s nothing to do with me?

462
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:46,350
By the way, how long have you been into drawing?

463
00:20:49,190 --> 00:20:50,350
Well,

464
00:20:50,710 --> 00:20:52,200
you’re just getting started, right?

465
00:20:52,810 --> 00:20:54,610
He has just discovered his passion.

466
00:20:54,630 --> 00:20:55,440
That’s why.

467
00:20:55,830 --> 00:20:57,220
Q,

468
00:20:57,740 --> 00:21:01,890
do you know that Toey actually planned to study medicine?

469
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:04,740
Why did you end up studying Fine Arts then?

470
00:21:12,230 --> 00:21:13,950
Here you go.

471
00:21:14,660 --> 00:21:15,200
- Thank you.
- 	You order the same one every day.

472
00:21:15,230 --> 00:21:16,270
Aren’t you bored of it?

473
00:21:16,310 --> 00:21:18,610
You’re good at making this drink.

474
00:21:18,670 --> 00:21:20,610
Are you saying I’m not good at making others?

475
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:22,790
No.

476
00:21:22,820 --> 00:21:24,560
That’s not what I mean.

477
00:21:25,590 --> 00:21:26,720
I’m kidding.

478
00:21:27,580 --> 00:21:29,650
Are you planning to study medicine?

479
00:21:31,580 --> 00:21:33,260
My mom wants me to.

480
00:21:33,780 --> 00:21:34,990
Do you like it?

481
00:21:35,210 --> 00:21:38,380
But I still don’t know what I like and what I want to do.

482
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:41,190
I’m not particularly good at anything, either.

483
00:21:41,210 --> 00:21:43,560
You still have time.

484
00:21:44,090 --> 00:21:46,760
One day, you’ll figure it out.

485
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:49,980
Hopefully, I will.

486
00:21:50,030 --> 00:21:52,780
But don’t pressure yourself.

487
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:54,060
Just take your time.

488
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:56,560
Sure.

489
00:21:56,620 --> 00:21:57,950
Thank you, Oh.

490
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:58,660
Okay.

491
00:21:58,690 --> 00:21:59,930
I’ll get back to work.

492
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:37,120
You’re zoning out, huh?

493
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:37,940
What’s on your mind?

494
00:22:37,970 --> 00:22:39,530
Q, it hurts.

495
00:22:41,380 --> 00:22:42,640
Here you go.

496
00:22:43,030 --> 00:22:44,130
Be careful. It’s hot.

497
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:45,330
Thank you.

498
00:22:46,990 --> 00:22:48,700
By the way,

499
00:22:48,740 --> 00:22:52,030
how about the work you’re submitting to the gallery?

500
00:22:52,050 --> 00:22:53,260
The one Phum messed up.

501
00:22:55,730 --> 00:22:57,730
Damn it. What can I do?

502
00:22:58,480 --> 00:22:59,920
I can’t do anything about it, can I?

503
00:22:59,950 --> 00:23:01,350
I’ll just paint a new one and submit it next year.

504
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:01,920
Shit.

505
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,100
Hey?

506
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:05,570
But it’s your dream, isn’t it?

507
00:23:05,610 --> 00:23:06,770
Don’t say that.

508
00:23:06,810 --> 00:23:08,510
It just makes me feel worse.

509
00:23:08,550 --> 00:23:09,430
What do you think I should do?

510
00:23:09,450 --> 00:23:10,350
See how it looks now?

511
00:23:15,730 --> 00:23:17,100
I just need to admit it.

512
00:23:17,130 --> 00:23:19,100
What are you two talking about?

513
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:21,040
It’s adult’s stuff.

514
00:23:21,450 --> 00:23:23,200
Juniors like you shouldn’t get involved.

515
00:23:29,360 --> 00:23:30,710
I asked Peem.

516
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:37,950
Q, what are you drawing?

517
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:39,850
I don’t get it.

518
00:23:41,550 --> 00:23:42,480
Hello?

519
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:44,300
(I’m thirsty.)

520
00:23:45,620 --> 00:23:46,740
Who’s this?

521
00:23:47,370 --> 00:23:49,140
(You can’t recognize your creditor’s voice?)

522
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:52,770
How did you get my number?

523
00:23:53,230 --> 00:23:55,040
I told you I’m thirsty.

524
00:23:55,470 --> 00:23:58,060
I’m busy.

525
00:23:58,080 --> 00:23:59,990
But I’m thirsty.

526
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:02,360
(Or do you want me to tell your friends?)

527
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:07,180
(You’d better be fast)

528
00:24:07,360 --> 00:24:09,180
(because I don’t know when I will let it slip.)

529
00:24:12,130 --> 00:24:13,180
Where are you?

530
00:24:13,730 --> 00:24:14,920
Engineering Faculty’s canteen.

531
00:24:14,970 --> 00:24:16,130
Hurry here.

532
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:19,800
I’ll be right back.

533
00:24:20,530 --> 00:24:21,580
Where are you going?

534
00:24:21,750 --> 00:24:22,430
I’m running an errand.

535
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:23,600
I’ll be right back.

536
00:24:32,670 --> 00:24:33,600
What do you want?

537
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:38,260
I’m thirsty.

538
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:39,590
Go buy the drink for me.

539
00:24:40,370 --> 00:24:43,880
[Cooked to Order Dishes]

540
00:24:44,910 --> 00:24:45,590
What?

541
00:24:46,140 --> 00:24:46,920
Hurry up.

542
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:57,140
Water, please.

543
00:25:02,510 --> 00:25:03,310
Here you are.

544
00:25:06,140 --> 00:25:07,400
I don’t drink water.

545
00:25:08,810 --> 00:25:09,920
Then what do you want?

546
00:25:18,430 --> 00:25:18,950
Here you are.

547
00:25:22,530 --> 00:25:24,300
I don’t like this red one either.

548
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:34,720
I don’t drink this fizzy green drink.

549
00:25:35,550 --> 00:25:36,860
It’s unhealthy.

550
00:25:43,990 --> 00:25:44,560
What?

551
00:25:45,030 --> 00:25:45,650
Be fast.

552
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:47,540
Buy me lunch after this.

553
00:26:01,540 --> 00:26:02,960
Did he freaking eat poops or something?

554
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:10,800
Why?

555
00:26:11,540 --> 00:26:13,190
Is the food at my faculty not good?

556
00:26:14,330 --> 00:26:16,510
It’s not good because I’m eating with you.

557
00:26:21,690 --> 00:26:23,690
Tan won’t see us, will he?

558
00:26:24,390 --> 00:26:25,690
He’s still in class.

559
00:26:26,070 --> 00:26:27,130
You didn’t go to class?

560
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:30,760
Just eat.

561
00:26:34,990 --> 00:26:35,550
Here.

562
00:26:37,770 --> 00:26:38,750
What are you doing?

563
00:26:40,890 --> 00:26:41,840
What are you playing, huh?

564
00:26:42,110 --> 00:26:42,960
Eat.

565
00:26:44,380 --> 00:26:45,200
Don’t.

566
00:26:45,260 --> 00:26:46,160
I can feed myself.

567
00:26:48,970 --> 00:26:49,810
Look at what you did.

568
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:50,810
It’s dirty.

569
00:26:56,890 --> 00:26:57,750
What? Why are you looking at me?

570
00:26:57,770 --> 00:26:58,430
Eat.

571
00:27:24,010 --> 00:27:26,170
You said he’s in class, didn’t you?

572
00:27:26,530 --> 00:27:28,090
Who knew his class would finish early, huh?

573
00:27:28,140 --> 00:27:28,880
